@startuml seq-batch-inference
title Async Batch Inference — Enterprise ML Platform (MVP phase)

skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam roundcorner 5

actor "Клиент" as Client
participant "API Gateway\n(Kong/Envoy)" as GW
participant "Batch Service\n(Python)" as Batch
participant "PostgreSQL" as PG
participant "Kafka\n(batch-jobs)" as Kafka
participant "Batch Workers\n(KEDA)" as Workers
participant "S3\n(Input / Output)" as S3
participant "Kafka\n(batch-jobs-dlq)" as DLQ

== Отправка batch-задания (FSM: → Submitted → Queued) ==

Client -> GW : POST /v1/batch/jobs\n{model_id, input_s3_uri, output_s3_uri, priority}
GW -> Batch : REST forward (аутентификация пройдена)

Batch -> PG : INSERT batch_jobs\n(state=SUBMITTED, tenant_id, model_id,\ninput_uri, idempotency_key)
PG --> Batch : job_id

Batch -> Kafka : produce BatchJobSubmitted\n{job_id, model_id, input_s3_uri,\noutput_s3_uri, tenant_id}
note right of Kafka
  Topic: batch-jobs
  RF=3, retention=3d
  KEDA ScaledObject: масштабирует
  Batch Workers по kafka lag
end note

Batch -> PG : UPDATE state=QUEUED
Batch --> GW : 202 Accepted {job_id, state: QUEUED}
GW --> Client : 202 Accepted {job_id}\n(используйте GET /v1/batch/jobs/{id} для статуса)

== Обработка Batch Workers ==

note right of Workers
  KEDA: scale-from-zero по kafka lag.
  При lag > 100 — добавляет workers.
  При lag = 0 — масштабирует до min=1.
end note

Kafka -> Workers : consume BatchJobSubmitted\n(CG: batch-workers)
Workers -> PG : UPDATE state=RUNNING

Workers -> S3 : GET input_s3_uri\n(потоковое чтение batch файла)
S3 --> Workers : input data stream

loop Обработка записей батчами (chunk_size=500)
    Workers -> Workers : InferenceService.Predict\n(local gRPC, GPU)

    alt Transient error (timeout, GPU unavailable)
        note right of Workers
          Retry с exponential backoff (NFR-208, max 3 попытки):
          attempt 1: wait 1s
          attempt 2: wait 2s (+jitter)
          attempt 3: wait 4s (+jitter)
          Max attempts: 3
          После 3 неудач → DLQ (batch-jobs-dlq)
        end note
        Workers -> Workers : retry (exponential backoff + jitter)
    end
end

Workers -> S3 : PUT output_s3_uri\n(результаты predictions)
S3 --> Workers : OK

Workers -> PG : UPDATE state=COMPLETED,\noutput_s3_uri, completed_at, records_processed
Workers -> Kafka : produce BatchJobCompleted\n{job_id, output_s3_uri, records_processed}

== Обработка неуспешных заданий (DLQ) ==

alt Превышены все попытки retry (persistent failure)
    note right of Workers
      После 3 неудачных попыток (NFR-208) сообщение
      направляется в Dead Letter Queue.
      Job FSM: RUNNING → FAILED.
    end note
    Workers -> DLQ : produce FailedBatchJob\n{job_id, error, attempt_count, last_error}
    Workers -> PG : UPDATE state=FAILED,\nfailure_reason, failed_at

    note right of DLQ
      Topic: batch-jobs-dlq
      Retention=7d.
      Инженер анализирует и
      при необходимости reprocesses вручную.
    end note
end

== Polling результата клиентом ==

Client -> GW : GET /v1/batch/jobs/{job_id}
GW -> Batch : REST forward
Batch -> PG : SELECT state, output_s3_uri,\nrecords_processed WHERE job_id=?
PG --> Batch : job status

alt state = COMPLETED
    Batch --> GW : 200 OK\n{state: COMPLETED, output_s3_uri, records_processed}
    GW --> Client : 200 OK {job details}
    Client -> S3 : GET output_s3_uri\n(скачать результаты)
else state = RUNNING / QUEUED
    Batch --> GW : 200 OK {state: RUNNING, progress_pct}
    GW --> Client : 200 OK {state: RUNNING}\n(повторить через 30s)
else state = FAILED
    Batch --> GW : 200 OK {state: FAILED, failure_reason}
    GW --> Client : 200 OK {state: FAILED}
end

note over Client, S3
  SLA batch: ≤30 мин для light jobs (≤100K записей),
  ≤2 ч для heavy jobs (до 10M записей) — NFR-108.
  Polling интервал рекомендован: 30s.
end note

@enduml